# Self-Improvement Protocol

After completing each major task or hitting a gotcha, create or update cursor rules in `.cursor/rules/` to help future sessions.

## When to Create/Update Rules
- Hit an unexpected API behavior or data format issue
- Discovered a Durham-specific data quirk (missing fields, weird zoning codes, geometry issues)
- Found a library configuration that was non-obvious (GDAL, PostGIS, deck.gl, etc.)
- Identified a performance optimization that matters
- Found a UDO rule edge case not captured in `udo_rules.json`

## Rule File Naming
- `gotcha-{topic}.mdc` for specific issues (e.g., `gotcha-arcgis-pagination.mdc`)
- Update existing rules when adding to a known topic

## Format
Keep rules concise (<50 lines), with concrete examples of what went wrong and how to fix it.
